# tag-mappings.folk
# Maps physical AprilTag IDs to logical booklet page names
# This makes booklets portable across different Folk installations

set this tag-mappings

# Each Folk installation prints tags with their own numeric IDs
# This file creates the mapping: physical tag â†’ logical page name

# Example mappings for Folk February booklet
# Adjust these numbers to match YOUR printed tags

# Day 01: Trace
Claim tag 100 is page folk-february-01-L
Claim tag 101 is page folk-february-01-R

# Day 02: Gravity
Claim tag 102 is page folk-february-02-L
Claim tag 103 is page folk-february-02-R

# Day 03: Echo
Claim tag 104 is page folk-february-03-L
Claim tag 105 is page folk-february-03-R

# ... continue for all 28 days ...

# Day 28: Memory
Claim tag 154 is page folk-february-28-L
Claim tag 155 is page folk-february-28-R

# Cover page
Claim tag 99 is page folk-february-cover

# ============================================
# HOW TO USE THIS:
# ============================================
#
# 1. Print AprilTags with sequential IDs (e.g., 100-155)
# 2. Update the mappings above to match your printed tags
# 3. The booklet programs will work with your tag numbers!
#
# Different installations can use different tag ranges:
#   - Installation A: tags 100-155
#   - Installation B: tags 200-255
#   - Installation C: tags 500-555
#
# Just update this mapping file for each installation.
#
# ============================================

puts "Tag mappings loaded for Folk February booklet"
puts "Using tags 100-155 (adjust in tag-mappings.folk for your installation)"
